    <h2>I. Setting Sail: A Word Before We Begin</h2>
    <p>
      There is an ocean inside every one of us. It is vast and unknown, hiding storms — and hiding treasure.
      Most people spend their whole lives gazing at it from the shore. But there are always a few who untie
      the mooring lines and steer their ship into the wind.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>LevelUp Land is the archipelago built for those people.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      We believe growth is not a slogan — it is a voyage that can be seen, recorded, and rewarded.
      Across this archipelago, every day of quiet persistence is an anchor weighed and a sail unfurled,
      every completed quest is a medal earned at sea, and every battle in the Arena is a trial faced
      head-on against the waves. The archipelago remembers every nautical mile you travel — and it
      answers with real rewards.
    </p>
    <blockquote>
      <p>Sail every day, harvest along the way. — The Voyager's Creed of LevelUp Land</p>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>II. The Problem We Set Out to Solve</h2>
    <p>
      This era has never lacked opportunities. What it lacks is <strong>persistence</strong>. Trends come and go,
      campaigns open and close, and users migrate between countless isolated events — their effort never
      accumulates, their loyalty never pays off. Project teams face the same frustration: budgets are spent,
      and what they buy is usually a one-time passerby, not a long-term companion.
    </p>
    <p>LevelUp Land's answer: <strong>make growth itself the single thread that runs through everything.</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>For users</strong>: every check-in, every quest, and every Arena battle on the platform flows into one continuous growth curve. The longer you persist, the higher you stand — and the richer the reward tiers within your reach.</li>
      <li><strong>For project teams</strong>: you are no longer facing a crowd of anonymous drifters, but an archipelago of voyagers with levels, history, and activity profiles. Your rewards flow precisely to the people who genuinely keep showing up.</li>
      <li><strong>For the platform</strong>: we are not resellers of traffic. A substantial share of the funds the platform retains from its games flows back as growth incentives for users, forming a virtuous cycle of "participate → grow → get rewarded → participate more deeply."</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>III. The Map of the Archipelago: Three Products</h2>
    <p>LevelUp Land is made up of three main islands — each a chapter of its own, all bound together by the same growth storyline:</p>

    <h3>⛵ Level · The Voyager's Path</h3>
    <p>
      This is the archipelago's main shipping lane. Open your Voyage Map and 8 islands rise one after another
      on the horizon: from the shallows where rookies weigh anchor, to the treasure atoll at the edge of the mist.
      Complete one "Today's Voyage" (the daily check-in quest) each day and your journey advances one step;
      accumulate 30 voyages and you land on the next island. Sustained streaks unlock rewards of higher rarity —
      Common, Rare, Epic, Legendary, tier upon tier. There are no shortcuts here — only the real wake you leave
      behind, day after day.
    </p>

    <h3>🗺️ Quest · The Bounty Guild</h3>
    <p>
      Bounty quests from project teams across the ecosystem are posted here. Follow, join, try, create —
      complete a quest to win rewards from the project team plus platform Growth Points.
      For voyagers, this is the supply port: every bounty feeds both your wallet and your level.
      For project teams, it is a stretch of high-quality waters filtered by the growth system itself.
    </p>

    <h3>⚔️ Arena · The Proving Grounds of Courage</h3>
    <p>
      The whirlpool waters at the deepest reach of the archipelago — and the heart of this whitepaper.
      Arena is LevelUp Land's competitive division: a sea of trials made up of multiple game worlds.
      Each world is a standalone arena with its own theme, narrative, and economic parameters,
      but all of them share one iron law: <strong>the rules are written into smart contracts,
      and no one — including the platform itself — can tamper with them.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Arena's first world is <strong>NU World</strong>: 100 warriors enter, the draw is randomized on-chain,
      and the tiers of fate are revealed on the spot — one is crowned Sovereign, some return in glory,
      and some fall and become Spirits, yet hold a vote that shapes the destiny of the entire Epoch.
      As the map expands, more parallel worlds will rise from these waters.
    </p>

    <h2>IV. The Arena Economic Model: NU World, the First World, as Our Example</h2>
    <p>
      Every game world under the Arena division carries its own economic parameters. This chapter uses the
      first world now live — <strong>NU World</strong> — as its working sample. It is deployed on
      BNB Smart Chain (BSC) and settles in USDT. Its economic model pursues three things:
      <strong>transparent rules, a high rate of funds flowing back to players, and long-term strategy
      outweighing single-round luck</strong>. Future worlds may carry different parameters, but all of them
      will follow the same design principles and contract-level transparency.
    </p>

    <h3>4.1 Gameplay at a Glance</h3>
    <p>
      NU World's core loop fits in one sentence: <strong>each round, 100 warriors each purchase one
      "Battle Soul" NFT; once sold out, a verifiable on-chain random number draws the round and assigns
      the tiers of fate on the spot; every 11 rounds form an Epoch, the fallen warriors endorse leaders
      with the votes in their hands, and at the Epoch's finale the "Grand Chieftain" is crowned and the
      grand prize pool is settled.</strong>
      Each address may buy one ticket per round; if a round doesn't sell out within 24 hours, the entire
      round is cancelled and fully refunded.
      For step-by-step instructions on joining, the tier titles, claiming, and voting, see the
      <a href="/en/arena/">Arena Guide</a> — the rest of this chapter focuses on what the guide doesn't cover:
      how the funds flow, and why this economy is sustainable.
    </p>
    <p>
      NU World runs <strong>multiple battlefields at different ticket prices</strong> in parallel: a light
      battlefield at 1 USDT, alongside high-stakes battlefields at larger amounts. All battlefields share
      one and the same rule set and distribution ratios, with prizes and fund flows <strong>scaling
      proportionally</strong> with the ticket price (the contract computes every allocation as a fixed
      multiple of the ticket price).
      <strong>For readability, this chapter uses the 1 USDT battlefield as its example</strong> — for other
      battlefields, simply multiply every amount below by the ticket-price multiple.
    </p>

    <h3>4.2 Per-Round Fund Allocation: Where Every 100 USDT Goes</h3>
    <p>
      Taking the 1 USDT battlefield as the example, a sold-out round holds 100 USDT in the pool, allocated
      by fixed contract ratios that no one can change (the "Share" column below is identical across all
      ticket-price battlefields):
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrap"><table>
      <thead><tr><th>Destination</th><th>Amount</th><th>Share</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Round prizes (paid to 56 winners)</strong></td><td>90.25 USDT</td><td>90.25%</td><td>Claimable right after the draw, no lock-up</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Epoch grand prize pool</strong></td><td>5 USDT</td><td>5%</td><td>Accumulates over 11 rounds, settled at the Epoch's end</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Platform reserve</strong></td><td>4.75 USDT</td><td>4.75%</td><td>A portion feeds the Growth Incentive Pool, flowing back to Level users (see Chapter V)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table></div>
    <p>
      In other words, <strong>over 95% of each round's funds flow back to participants as prizes and the
      grand prize pool</strong>; and of the 4.75% the platform retains, a further portion continues on as
      growth incentives for all users.
    </p>

    <h3>4.3 The Prize Structure: How 90.25 USDT Is Spread</h3>
    <p>
      The round prizes are no exercise in flat egalitarianism — they trace a curve that is steep yet
      restrained, preserving the peak dream of an overnight coronation while letting plenty of players
      walk away with a harvest:
      1 Sovereign claims 14.25 USDT alone (a 14.25× return), 5 Bannerlords take 5.70 each, 10 Glory
      leaders take 2.85 each, and 40 Survivors take 0.475 each — summing to exactly 90.25 USDT
      (all figures for the 1 USDT battlefield; return multiples are identical across every ticket price).
      <strong>Each round, 56% of participants walk away with USDT, and 16% ascend to a leader's seat.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      The remaining 44 fallen warriors are the most elegant piece of this economy: their Battle Souls
      become Spirits, each granted a vote that influences who claims the Epoch grand prize — defeat is
      not wiped to zero, but converted into a stake in the next layer of the game.
    </p>

    <h3>4.4 The Epoch Grand Prize Pool: Turning Single-Round Luck into a Long Game</h3>
    <p>
      5% of every round's ticket pool feeds the grand prize pool (5 USDT per round on the 1 USDT
      battlefield), accumulating over 11 rounds into a <strong>55 USDT</strong> Epoch grand prize,
      settled at the Epoch's finale on a <strong>90% / 10%</strong> split: <strong>49.5 USDT</strong>
      goes to the leaders on the Endorsement Board, and <strong>5.5 USDT</strong> is distributed at
      random among the Spirits who cast endorsement votes (roughly 1% of voters are drawn as the lucky
      recipients). On high-stakes battlefields, the grand prize pool scales proportionally with the
      ticket price.
    </p>
    <p>
      That 5% acts as a lever: it welds 11 independent draw rounds into a single reputation race
      spanning the entire Epoch — leaders must court the Spirits' votes, and every Spirit's vote
      carries real economic weight. A single round's outcome is only the opening move; the Epoch's
      coronation is the final chapter.
    </p>

    <h3>4.5 The Fairness Pledge</h3>
    <p>
      Every ratio above is hard-coded into the smart contract; once a round opens, no one — the platform
      included — can change it. The draw's randomness is supplied by Chainlink VRF v2.5, with the
      generation process and cryptographic proof fully on-chain and verifiable. Prizes are claimable
      the moment the draw completes, with no lock-up; rounds that fail to sell out are automatically
      refunded in full. For technical details and step-by-step instructions, see the fairness section
      of the <a href="/en/arena/">Arena Guide</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>V. The Growth Incentive Pool: The Ocean Gives Back</h2>
    <p>
      This is the crowning touch of LevelUp Land's economic design — the point where the two storylines
      of growth and competition converge.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>From every round of every Arena world, the platform retains a portion of the funds
      (for NU World's 1 USDT battlefield, a portion of the 4.75 USDT per-round reserve, scaling
      proportionally with ticket price on high-stakes battlefields) and continuously channels it into
      the Growth Incentive Pool.</strong>
      This pool is not spent on operations. It exists for one purpose only: <strong>rewarding the users
      who keep growing along the Level Voyage Map.</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Every war drum that sounds in the Arena stores up a reward for the voyagers of Level;</li>
      <li>Users who keep sailing every day and landing on new islands will earn rewards from the incentive pool at growth milestones (in forms including platform point boosts, Arena Battle Soul tickets, badges, and more benefits to come);</li>
      <li>The heat of competition feeds the persistence of growth, and growing users in turn form the healthiest soil for competition — between the two islands, the current never stops circulating.</li>
    </ul>
    <blockquote>
      <p>Elsewhere, the house keeps the rake. On LevelUp Land, it flows back to everyone who takes their growth seriously.</p>
    </blockquote>

